Pour @cold salted water{300%ml} into a #medium pot{} with a #tight-fitting lid{}.

Stir in the @rice{150%grams} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Cook for ~{10%minutes} then remove from the heat.

Keep covered for ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, trim the @courgette{1} and chop into 1cm cubes.

Trim the @carrot{1} then slice into ½ cm thick rounds (no need to peel).

Quarter the @lime{½}.

Trim and thinly slice the @scallion{1}.

Stir the @coconut milk{1%pack} (or shake the packet) to dissolve any lumps.

Drain the @tofu{180%grams} and pat dry with #kitchen paper{}. Coarsely grate the tofu.

Place a #large pan{} over high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Add the carrot and fry until tender, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Lower the heat to medium-high then add the tofu, courgette and @Thai Style Spice Mix{2%sachets} to the pan.

Fry until fragrant, stirring occasionally, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir through the @Red Thai Style Paste{1%sachet}, coconut milk and @Miso Paste{1%sachet}.

Cover and simmer for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a squeeze of lime juice to your curry. Loosen the sauce with a splash of @?water{to taste} if you feel it's too thick.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and more lime juice if you like.

Divide the rice between #bowls{} and top with the tofu Thai curry.

Finish with a sprinkling of scallion and as much of the @Dried Chilli Flakes{1%sachet} as you like (use less if you don't like spice).

Serve any remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.